The paper deals with the complexity hierarchy in sub-linear time, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves descriptive complexity theory, which is a subfield of logic and computability theory, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) another likely sub-category. The paper discusses the structure of the polylogarithmic time hierarchy, which involves algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the absence of complete problems, which is a topic in discrete mathematics, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category as well.
